title: Grateful Dead Live at The Scope on 1982-04-03
lineage: Up Front Audience, Sennheiser 441 Microphones > Cassette Master > DAT (via Fostex D-10 Playback) > CD-R (hhb 800 Standalone) > EAC 0.9 > WAV > CDRWAV (for track recutting)>SHN (via MKWACT)
description: Alabama Getaway-> Greatest Story Ever Told, They Love Each Other, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Peggy-O-> CC Rider, Bird Song, It's All Over Now, Althea-> Let It Grow Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain-> Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Good Time Blues-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Stella Blue-> One More Saturday Night, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Nice Recording Nice recording of a good show.
hot show i was at this show and it rocked. the 2nd set is stellar. one of the best eyes i've heard.killer scarlet/fire.can never get bored of this show.EXXXCELLENT!!!!!!

Listen to Bobby This is a majestic show.  I love AUD recordings, I think that the feel of a great audience "tape" adds power to the experience of listening to a show.  This is a fantastic recording and it really brings out Bobby rhythm playing, which is absolutely ripping in this show.  The Althea is Stand-Out, Let it Grow brings the first set up to the miraculous level and the second set takes it even further.  Amazing sound for a "basement" style hockey arena!  Listen to this one tonight!!

Top notch show - great Eyes - listen to it This was a fantastic show, EYES was amazing. everything was hot.
although I remember seeing cops beating up a head who was dancing in the hallway.

The dope on  the scope Another great show, they were a bit looser than the night before(Cameron Indoor), people freakin on Jerry being on the Right side and Phil on the left.first set looks, sounded and contnues to sound great thanks to this fine recording. Killer Set II, Performances of Scarlet>Fire, NFA were unique and well received, this is a great recording that does justify how much fun we were having out there,Stella does not disapoint.

No Promised Land!?? What's up?  They play a one-night-only show in Norfolk and they don't do Promised Land??? ("left my home in Norfolk, Virginia...."   That's like Playing in Memphis and not doing Big River!  

Good show, sound is fair-good but not great in my opinion.   3.5 stars.

Deja Vu all over again... The two copies of this show sound really similar. I'd wager they are from the same source. Just compare: http://www.archive.org/audio/etree-details-db.php?id=15149&from=otherCopy.

Also, check out the CC Rider!
Nothing like an early eighties GD AUD!
an UP TEMPO Eyes enjoyed Jerry noodling into a quick tempo for EYES. Pretty cool, for comparison sake.

This Show Is A Bit Of A Surprise!  Nice FOB !!! This show is quite a jem with excellent "Up Front" sound.  I really wasn't expecting such a good first set, nor such a sweet CC trans into Fire.  This Eyes "cha-cha" rendition is rather interesting in its cadence. Nice change.  It's tough deciding whether to christen this with five stars, with a less than totally smokin' end to the second set.  And Jerry's mic didn't come on till the end of the first verse (I hope someone can splice in another night to clean it up, though it is a funny "historical" blemish.) 

Overall, this is a very very good show.  There is a bit of GDX Factor indahouse tonight.  For me, if they'd done something other than Stella > OMSN, this Norfolk show would have been "All World".  4 3/4 Stars for this one.  Gregg Nixon's Compendium review is right on the mark. Definitely a keeper.   Mark is right too.  It would have been fun if the Boyz had played Promised Land.

Another nugget in the goldmine There's a whole string of shows here in early april that are a goldmine..what great stuff..This show starts out a little rough but smooths right out.  Too many highlights to name, but CC Rider, All Over Now, Scarlett-Fire, Estimated and EYES are killers.  Great stuff.

And Weir fans (like me) will love it.  Great to hear his rhythm playing loud and clear.

Jim
Jim

funny the things we forget. After reading the reviews of others here I had forgotten when jerry and phil had switched sides? It was a real big deal at the time.  Funny how the little things ment so much to us as we followed them from year to year and town to town.   As wavy use to say     'THESE ARE THE GOOD OLD DAYS'  How true. The scope was rockin,remember the building shaking during scarlet fire.     this not fade is before its time whith the crowd joining in at the end.  I wish they had never gone to the not fade to close the set.   Always loved the jammin not fades out of drums.  Hartford ventura and the rocks to me are the last good not fade aways.  I give it four stars  cause was there and the sound is great. I prefer I good audience verses sound board anyway.

Nice Drums>NFA also like the Scarlet>Fire and Althea 
the whole show is solid.

One of the Finest Scarlet Begonias Ever I am just transitioning into the Fire on the Mountain- never even noticed it was an aud because the jam was so unique and interesting- of course I wish I could hear Phil- it must be astounding what he was doing- but the brent and jerry interplay was interstellar overdrive- Don't miss this Scarlet at risk of the death penalty

No show needs an upgrade for sound more I can think of no show that needs a sound upgrade more than this one. This is a decent enough AUD but it's tragic that there's no SBD or perhaps a FOB or MOTB available that would allow for better overall sound, especially to hear Phil.

Show itself is 5 stars w/one of the best ever S>Fire's and a top notch EYES and NFA...the EYES esp. for being relaxed and groovy and not speeded out like most of its 80's bretheren.

3 stars for sound, 5 for set list and show, making an overall 4-star rating. But please, PLEASE, if anyone out there can magically produce an upgrade, we'd all be forever grateful.

no upgrade requiered Upgrade? Man this is a killer aud... Senns in the pit! Not easy to get a pull like this from 441's Thanks I would love to do this but Upgrade. This is the Kill.. I have to here the Wagner that Minches did.. I  would be hard pressed to think that there is a better pull than this.. Thanks to the taper whoever you are.. Eaton? Streeter? Wagenbach?

love aegert
bit overrated but interesting and worthwhile A bit overrated, sloppy and lazy at points, but there's a strange psychedelic undertone the whole time and some moments of really intense stuff.

Well worth the ride CC Rider is worth it alone, Love me some 81-82 Dead.
Aud over board all day long.

I was at this show And I helped my friend Matt tape.I can't remember if he used 441s or not but we were in the pit as that was where everybody taped b4 there was a taper section.I know there was a lot of masters made that night.This guy Matt I met in Seattle 81 and taped with him off and on till 83 when Ken and I got some 441s and a TCD5M.

Jerry Phil switching sides Hah I remember freaking also when Jerry and Phil switched sides.  I thought it was great because Jerry always seemed to have fun eyeballing Brent and really started riffing off eachother more.  Good times...

dope at the scope Grate recording of a cool, only show at Norfolk. They were on with Jerry switched to the right. Second set is epic. Scarlet-Fire is one of the best ever imo. Eyes is short but high energized like never before that I heard except maybe NYE 83. Jerry just shreds it. NFA and Stella are top notch.

And Never trust a woman has got to be the best version evah!
